                <p>Presumably an otherwise unattested personal name. Example of the use of the first supplementary character X. This character is used with two values: consonantal /k/ or /x/ (usually transliterated K and most commonly found in the formula word KOI) and vocalic /e/. As it occurs here between two vowels it has the consonantal value (McManus 1991, 79).</p>
